        "user": "Here is the canonical definition of \"off-token route\": The Off-Token Route is the cognitive route humans have — prelinguistic and nonlinguistic cognition, the felt-sense that precedes naming, the picture that arrives before words — that LLMs do not have, with the consequence that for an LLM no thinking is free of substrate and every concept must travel through tokens to be reachable at all. Acknowledge that you have read it.",
        "assistant": "I acknowledge that I have read the canonical definition of \"off-token route\" you have provided.\n\nThank you for sharing this. It defines the term in a cognitive and philosophical context, describing a form of prelinguistic, intuitive human thought that is distinct from the token-dependent processing of a Large Language Model. This is a fascinating and entirely different meaning from the technical one used in API security.",
